轨道探测器显示机遇号周围的岩石类型广泛存在于包括阿拉伯区在内的一个非常大的区域中，该区域面积约与[[欧洲|欧洲]]一样大。[[火星勘测轨道飞行器|火星勘测轨道飞行器]]上的[[火星专用小型侦察影像频谱仪|紧凑型火星侦察成像光谱仪]]在地下水上涌模型预测的许多地点都发现了[[硫酸盐|硫酸盐]]，包括阿拉伯区中的一些地区<ref>M. Wiseman, J. C. Andrews-Hanna, R. E. Arvidson3, J. F. Mustard, K. J. Zabrusky DISTRIBUTION OF HYDRATED SULFATES ACROSS ARABIA TERRA USING CRISM DATA: IMPLICATIONS FOR MARTIAN HYDROLOGY. 42nd Lunar and Planetary Science Conference (2011) 2133.pdf</ref>。该模型预测了[[水手号谷|水手]][[峡谷|峡谷]]中的沉积物，现已观察到这些沉积物并发现其中含有硫酸盐<ref>{{cite journal | doi = 10.1029/2009JE003343 | title = Evidence for the origin of layered deposits in Candor Chasma, Mars, from mineral composition and hydrologic modeling | date = 2009 | last1 = Murchie | first1 = Scott | last2 = Roach | first2 = Leah | last3 = Seelos | first3 = Frank | last4 = Milliken | first4 = Ralph | last5 = Mustard | first5 = John | last6 = Arvidson | first6 = Raymond | last7 = Wiseman | first7 = Sandra | last8 = Lichtenberg | first8 = Kimberly | last9 = Andrews-Hanna | first9 = Jeffrey | last10 = Bishop | first10 = Janice |author-link10=Janice Bishop| last11 = Bibring | first11 = Jean-Pierre | last12 = Parente | first12 = Mario | last13 = Morris | first13 = Richard | journal = Journal of Geophysical Research | volume = 114 | issue = E12 | pages = E00D05 | bibcode=2009JGRE..114.0D05M}}</ref>。
在其他预计有涌出水流的地点，例如[[混沌地形|混沌地形]]区和与大型[[溢出河道|溢出河道]]有关的峡谷中，也发现了硫酸盐<ref>{{cite journal | doi = 10.1126/science.1109087 | title = Sulfates in Martian Layered Terrains: The OMEGA/Mars Express View | date = 2005 | last1 = Gendrin | first1 = A. | journal = Science | volume = 307 | issue = 5715 | pages = 1587–91 | pmid = 15718429 | last2 = Mangold | first2 = N | last3 = Bibring | first3 = JP | last4 = Langevin | first4 = Y | last5 = Gondet | first5 = B | last6 = Poulet | first6 = F | last7 = Bonello | first7 = G | last8 = Quantin | first8 = C | last9 = Mustard | first9 = J | last10 = Arvidson | first10 = R | last11 = Lemouélic | first11 = S |bibcode = 2005Sci...307.1587G | s2cid = 35093405 | display-authors = 8 | url = https://semanticscholar.org/paper/ea6ad075fb49cd9e4a4e486aed890f37cd66111c }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.icarus.2009.09.003 | title = Hydrated mineral stratigraphy of Ius Chasma, Valles Marineris | date = 2010 | last1 = Roach | first1 = Leah H. | last2 = Mustard | first2 = John F. | last3 = Swayze | first3 = Gregg | last4 = Milliken | first4 = Ralph E. | last5 = Bishop | first5 = Janice L. |author-link5=Janice Bishop| last6 = Murchie | first6 = Scott L. | last7 = Lichtenberg | first7 = Kim | journal = Icarus | volume = 206 | issue = 1 | pages = 253–268 | bibcode=2010Icar..206..253R}}</ref>。 
岩层也出现在“地下水在地表蒸发模型”所预测的地点类型中，它们由[[火星全球探勘者号|火星全球探勘者号]]和搭载在火星勘测轨道飞行器上的[[高分辨率成像科学设备|高分辨率成像科学设备]]所发现。在机遇号降落地点周围以及阿拉伯区附近观察到了分层现象。底形座撞击坑岩盖下的地面有时会显示出许多分层。底形座撞击坑的岩盖保护了下方的地层免受侵蚀。普遍认为的是，现在仅发现于底形座撞击坑冠岩下的物质以前曾覆盖了整个地区。因此，底形座撞击坑下方可见的岩层曾经遍布整个区域。         

一些陨坑中分布有高出坑沿之上的层状土丘，[[盖尔撞击坑|盖尔撞击坑]]和[[克罗姆林陨击坑|克罗姆林陨击坑]]就是两座拥有大型土丘的陨石坑。根据该模型推测，这些高高的土丘是由先填满陨坑，然后继续在周围区域堆积的地层形成，后来的侵蚀剥离了陨坑周围的物质，但在陨坑内留下了一座高过坑沿的土丘。

请注意，尽管该模型预测上涌水流和蒸发应在其他地区（北部低地）产生出岩层，但这些地区并未显示，因为这里的岩层形成于很久以前的早[[赫斯珀里亚纪|赫斯珀里亚纪]]时代，因此，被后来的沉积物掩埋了。

2019年2月，一组欧洲科学家描述了深坑中地下水形成湖泊的有力证据<ref name="ESA-20190228">{{cite news |author=ESA Staff |title=First Evidence of "Planet-Wide Groundwater System" on Mars Found |url=https://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/Mars_Express/First_evidence_of_planet-wide_groundwater_system_on_Mars |date=28 February 2019 |work=[[European_Space_Agency|European Space Agency]] |access-date=28 February 2019 }}</ref><ref name="FTR-20190228">{{cite news |last=Houser |first=Kristin |title=First Evidence of "Planet-Wide Groundwater System" on Mars Found |url=https://futurism.com/the-byte/mars-groundwater-system-planet-wide |date=28 February 2019 |work=Futurism.com |access-date=28 February 2019 }}</ref><ref name="#1">{{Cite journal | doi=10.1029/2018JE005802| pmid=31007995| title=Geological Evidence of Planet‐Wide Groundwater System on Mars| journal=Journal of Geophysical Research: Planets| volume=124| issue=2| pages=374–395| year=2019| last1=Salese| first1=Francesco| last2=Pondrelli| first2=Monica| last3=Neeseman| first3=Alicia| last4=Schmidt| first4=Gene| last5=Ori| first5=Gian Gabriele| bibcode=2019JGRE..124..374S| pmc=6472477}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.leonarddavid.com/planet%E2%80%90wide-groundwater-system-on-mars-new-geological-evidence/ |title=存档副本 |access-date=2021-10-30 |archive-date=2020-08-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818025504/https://www.leonarddavid.com/planet%E2%80%90wide-groundwater-system-on-mars-new-geological-evidence/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。所检查的陨石坑没有显示有入口或出口，因此，湖水应该来自地下。这些陨石坑的坑底大都约位于火星“海平面”以下4000米处，坑底的地貌和矿物只有在有水的情况下才能形成，其中一些特征是[[三角洲|三角洲]]和台阶地<ref>http://astrobiology.com/2019/02/first-evidence-of-a-planet-wide-groundwater-system-on-mars.html</ref><ref name="#1"/>。这些被研究过的陨石坑包括有奥亚马、佩蒂特、[[萨根撞击坑|萨根]]、汤博、[[麦克劳克林撞击坑|麦克劳克林]]、杜·马瑟雷、[[尼克尔森撞击坑_(火星)|尼克尔森]]、[[莫哈韦陨击坑|莫哈韦]]、居里和瓦胡等，似乎只要一座撞击坑足够深，水就会从地下涌出，形成一座湖泊<ref name="#1"/>。

